In [22]:



     


def gd(x,y,n):
    m=6
    c=3
    alpha=0.8
    len=x.shape[0]
    for r in range(n):
        y_pred=m*x +c
        cost=(1/len)*((y_pred-y)**2).sum()
        print('cost is ',cost)
        m=m-(-alpha/len)*((y-y_pred)*x).sum()
        c=c-(-alpha/len)*((y-y_pred).sum())
        print('m,c is',m,c)
        if cost<1:
            plt.scatter(x,y)
            plt.plot(x,y_pred)

In [90]:



     


# Function for Adjusted R-Square

def adj_r2(x, y):
    r2= lr.score(x, y)
    n= x.shape[0]
    p= x.shape[1]
    adjusted_r2= 1-(1-r2)*(n-1)(n-p-1)
    return adjusted_r2
